==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headway
<hw>Head"way`</hw> <pr>(-w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The progress made by a ship in motion; hence, progress or success
of any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Clear space under an arch,
girder, and the like, sufficient to allow of easy passing underneath;
clearance; headroom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>headword</ent>⟦br⟧
